<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Committee Rejects VMRO-DPMNE Claims </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Committee Rejects VMRO-DPMNE Claims </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2306184894 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2306184894 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Intelligence Agency -- Clean"] </F>
  [Text] Yesterday, the Parliament Committee for control 
over the work of the State Intelligence Agency announced the 
results of its surveillance of the agency documents. The 
Committee confirmed the intelligence service had not undertaken 
any operative or technical methods towards VMRO-DPMNE [Internal 
Macedonian Revolutionary Organization-Democratic Party for 
Macedonian National Unity], nor towards any other political 
party. The document presented to the public by Ljupco 
Georgievski is a forgery, as there is no original or any other 
document in the intelligence documentation under that number and 
date. The intelligence does not undertake measures and methods, 
but on individuals connected with foreign intelligence services 
or because of activities aimed at endangering the constitutional 
establishment of Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia -- FYROM], the Committee report states. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

