<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkish Planes Violate Airspace; Forced To Land </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turkish Planes Violate Airspace; Forced To Land </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2406164394 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1600 
GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2406164394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] We just received the following announcement from 
the Press Center of the Ministry of Defense: 
  On 23 June at 1040 [0740 GMT] the Air Force guard duty units 
noted a violation of Bulgaria's airspace committed by 21 light 
transportation aircraft flying from near the village of Radovets 
in Turkey, in two directions: Burgas and Sofia. 
  The Air Force guard duty aircraft were immediately placed in 
a state of readiness, which included the takeoff of fighters. 
The aircraft that violated Bulgarian airspace were forced to 
land at the airports of Saratovo and Sofia. A commission 
appointed by the Air Force commander is investigating the 
reasons the flight regulations were violated. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

