<H3> <TI>   Horn Praises Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Horn Praises Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406165894 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1600 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2406165894 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] An agreement on the government coalition has 
been drawn up. [passage omitted] The agreement will only become 
final if the Hungarian Socialist Party [MSZP] congress and the 
Alliance of Free Democrats [SZDSZ] convention adopt it on 
Sunday. [MSZP Chairman] Gyula Horn spoke highly of the agreement: 
  [Begin Horn recording] The MSZP and the SZDSZ are committed 
to an effective market economy supported by social guarantees. 
They take a stand for the guaranteeing of human and political 
rights, for parliamentary democracy and constitutional 
statehood. The joint goals of the MSZP and the SZDSZ are the 
guaranteeing of the independence and security of the Hungarian 
Republic and our country's joining the democratic community of 
the European peoples, in cooperation with neighbouring 
countries, and supporting the Hungarians living in neighboring 
countries. 
  The MSZP and the SZDSZ wish to lead the country out of the 
serious crisis with a sensible and resolute economy policy and a 
sensitive social policy. The two parties are well aware of the 
fact that the preconditions of this are the maintenance of 
social peace and the achievement and maintenance of a general 
agreement with the various groups and [word indistinct] of 
society. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

