<H3> <TI>   SZDSZ National Council Accepts Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SZDSZ National Council Accepts Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2506162594 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1400 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2506162594 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The National Council of the Alliance of Free 
Democrats [SZDSZ] has accepted the coalition agreement, and it 
will propose to the extraordinary delegates assembly, which is 
to convene tomorrow, that it should accept the agreement on 
principles of joint governing with the Hungarian Socialist Party 
[MSZP] and on the basic points of the government program. At 
the SZDSZ National Council the agreement received 50 votes in 
favor and five against. Four people abstained from voting. 
Party Chairman Ivan Petoe said that those SZDSZ members who 
cast their vote against the coalition agreement objected to the 
negotiations with the MSZP in the first place. The SZDSZ 
delegates assembly is not going to change the text of the 
coalition agreement. 

</TEXT>

