<F P=100> HUNGARY </F>
<H3> <TI>   KDNP Presidium Resigns After Election `Fiasco' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    KDNP Presidium Resigns After Election `Fiasco' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2506151194 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1200 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2506151194 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The presidium of the Christian Democratic People's 
Party [KDNP] has resigned. At a session of its national 
executive, Party Chairman Laszlo Surjan described the party's 
election performance as a fiasco, in spite of the fact that this 
time it received more votes than four years ago. The departing 
leader pointed out that the KDNP leadership must be renewed, and 
that this is why the presidium has quit its mandate. 

</TEXT>

