<H3> <TI>   KDH Names Electoral Leaders to 4 Constituencies </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    KDH Names Electoral Leaders to 4 Constituencies </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2706114594 Bratislava NARODNA OBRODA in Slovak 24 Jun 94 p 
2 </F>

<F P=103> AU2706114594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava NARODNA OBRODA </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report in the "From Yesterday's Briefings" </F>
column: "Christian Democratic Movement--Electoral Leaders: 
Dzurinda, Pittner, Carnogursky"] 
  [Text] The Christian Democratic Movement [KDH] leadership 
has approved the movement's election campaign. In east 
Slovakia, it will be led by [Minister of Transportation and 
Communications] Mikulas Dzurinda. Number two will be [KDH Deputy 
Chairman] Frantisek Miklosko. The number-one candidate in 
central Slovakia is [Interior Minister] Ladislav Pittner, number 
two is [Culture Minister] Lubo Roman. Number one in west 
Slovakia is [KDH Chairman] Jan Carnogursky, number two [Minister 
of Labor and Social Affairs] Julius Brocka. The election 
campaign in the Slovak capital, Bratislava, will be led by 
[Deputy Prime Minister] Ivan Simko. 

</TEXT>

