<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Kovac Confirms Privatization Policy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Kovac Confirms Privatization Policy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2506141494 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1000 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2506141494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1000 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In New York, President Michal Kovac confirmed the 
government's intention to vigorously continue the privatization 
process during his meeting with representatives of Merrill 
Lynch, an important U.S. investment and consulting company. 
Kovac considers the inability to analyze economic processes 
with sufficient precision as well as the poorly defined concept 
of a long-term orientation to be the reason for the slowdown in 
the transformation process last year. We consider the emergence 
of businesses that are able to develop and survive in the 
international market environment to be the main privatization 
objective, said Kovac, who is continuing his visit to the United 
States. 

</TEXT>

