<H3> <TI>   Budget Deficit Drops to Sk2.29 Billion in May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Budget Deficit Drops to Sk2.29 Billion in May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2706114294 Bratislava HOSPODARSKE NOVINY in Slovak 23 Jun 
94 p 2 </F>

<F P=103> AU2706114294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava HOSPODARSKE NOVINY </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "Temporary Growth of Deficit"] </F>
  [Text] Bratislava--The deficit of the state budget of the 
Slovak Republic in the first five months of this year developed 
more favorably than expected. By 31 May 1994, it declined to 
2.29 billion Slovak korunas [Sk] (from Sk3.8 billion at the end 
of April). As of 21 June 1994, the budget management of the 
Slovak Republic has been showing a deficit of Sk7.9 billion. 
This sum will, however, decrease by the end of the month 
because the surrendering of proceeds from the crucial taxes--the 
value-added tax and excise taxes--starts after the 23d day of 
every month. An analysis of the current deviation in the budget 
management of the Slovak Republic confirms that it is also 
influenced by the changed position of the Slovak Republic in the 
fulfillment of the payments agreement with the Czech Republic 
because Slovakia has now become the Czech Republic's creditor. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

