<H3> <TI>   British Soldier Killed at Gorazde Checkpoint </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    British Soldier Killed at Gorazde Checkpoint </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2706091794 London PRESS ASSOCIATION in English 0851 GMT 27 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2706091794 </F>
<F P=104>  London PRESS ASSOCIATION </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Teilo Colley, PA News] </F>
  [Text] A British soldier has been shot dead in Bosnia, the 
Ministry of Defence [MoD] said today. Private Sean Richard 
Taylor, 20, of Cleveland, was a member of the Duke of 
Wellington's Regiment. He was killed last night at an 
observation point at Gorazde, a Muslim enclave in the east of 
the country which is surrounded by Bosnian Serb forces. He was 
the sixth British soldier to die in Bosnia. The shooting came a 
few days after two British soldiers were injured when an 
explosion damaged their armoured vehicle six miles south-west of 
Maglaj in central Bosnia. The MoD said Pte. Taylor was manning 
an observation post which came under attack. He died from a 
single bullet. 

</TEXT>

