<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Croatian Enclave Under Serbian Artillery Attack </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Croatian Enclave Under Serbian Artillery Attack </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2606110394 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1000 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2606110394 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] One civilian was killed and three injured in last 
night's Serb artillery attack on Usora [Croatian enclave in 
northern Bosnia]. Doctors in Tesanj war hospital are fighting 
to save the lives of the wounded. There is fresh damage to 
residential buildings. Serbs are heavily shelling locations 
adjacent to the front line. From their strongholds in Putnikovo 
Brdo, Zeravica, and Stanovi, Serbs were shelling defense lines 
and the free Usora territory with mortars, tanks, and long-range 
shells until late last night. They also attempted an infantry 
breakthrough but Usora defenders prevented it. Fresh explosions 
were heard in the free Usora territory again this morning. 

</TEXT>

