<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-32529 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu123_i_94021" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-123 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  25 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Muslims Continue Firing on Serb Positions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Muslims Continue Firing on Serb Positions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2506131894 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1248 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2506131894 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Zvornik, June 25 (TANJUG) -- The Moslem forces 
continued firing on positions of the Bosnian Serb army in the 
past 24 hours in the northern, western, central and other parts 
of the Bosnian Serb republic. This is a flagrant violation of 
the agreement reached in Geneva by the two warring sides to 
refrain from military activity and which entered into force on 
June 10. The Moslem forces strongly attacked with all kinds of 
weapons including heavy artillery the area of Srbobran (former 
Donji Vakuf) and Mt Vlasic in central Bosnia-Herzegovina, TANJUG 
learns from Serb military sources. 
  A number of attacks were also registered in the area of 
Teslic, Doboj, Ozren, Gradacac, Orasje and Trebava, in 
northeastern Bosnia-Herzegovina. Moslem armed action was also 
registered in other northeastern parts of Bosnia -- in the 
Olovo-Kladanj direction, in the area of Mt Majevica and in the 
Zvornik area. Moslems launched artillery and mortar attacks on 
the town of Teslic without inflicting any casualties but causing 
considerable material damages on civilian facilities. 
  Joint forces of the Croat Defense Council (HVO) and the 
regular Croatian troops use anti-aircraft guns in their attacks 
on the Orasje front. The Moslems tried to inflitrate a 
sabotage-terrorist group in the Orasje part of the front 
Saturday morning but the group was routed, the press center of 
the First Krajina Corps of the Bosnian Serb army reports. 
  Moslem action did not stop along the Bihac-Krupa 
confrontation line in western Bosnia-Herzegovina, Serb military 
sources state. Moslems also continued attacks on Serb territory 
from the direction of Gorazde, Moslem enclave in eastern Bosnia 
which has been declared a safe area by the United Nations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

