<H3> <TI>   `Yugoslav-Korean Friendship Society' Founded </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Yugoslav-Korean Friendship Society' Founded </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406150794 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1432 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2406150794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 24 Jun (TANJUG) -- The Yugoslav-Korean 
Friendship Society was founded in Belgrade today, the society's 
newly formed main committee announced. The constituent 
assembly, attended by more than 200 participants, adopted the 
society's code of practice and elected the 15-member main 
committee. 
  Milorad Zecevic, director of Coca-Cola [as received], was 
elected as the society's president, and author Djurica Labovic 
as secretary. Yu Se-ung, ambassador of the Democratic People's 
Republic of Korea to Yugoslavia, addressed the participants in 
the constituent assembly, and thanked the founding committee for 
its efforts in forming the society. 

</TEXT>

