<F P=101> Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serb Convoy of 28 Tanks Moves Toward Podujeve </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serb Convoy of 28 Tanks Moves Toward Podujeve </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2406191294 Tirana TVSH Television Network in Albanian 1800 
GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2406191294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana TVSH Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Albanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At about 0500 this morning, a Serbian Army convoy 
made up of 28 tanks and seven transportation trucks, as well as 
other military equipment, moved from Prishtina in the direction 
of Podujeve on the Miloshev-Leban road. A characteristic of the 
Serb Army movements this time is that many Serb flags were seen 
placed above the tanks. 
  It is worthy of mention that in this region today, there 
were 
frequent flights by Serbian aircraft, and many military vehicles 
were observed on the streets of Prishtina, reports the Kosova 
Information Center. 

</TEXT>

