<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Disputes Arise Over Population Census </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Disputes Arise Over Population Census </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Serbs Protest Census Forms </H4>

<F P=102> LD2506173594 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1318 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2506173594 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Skopje, 25 Jun (TANJUG) -- The Democratic Alliance 
of Serbs in Macedonia [DSSM] today sent a public message to the 
citizens of Serb nationality instructing them to provide 
information for the P1 [population census] form only if the form 
is printed in two languages--Serbian and Macedonian--and to 
refuse to take part in the census if the form is printed only in 
Macedonian. 
  A statement released by the DSSM says that this message was 
sent to the Serbs in Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia -- FYROM] because some census collectors are trying to 
register the Serbs on forms printed in Macedonian, with the 
assistance of an official interpreter, which is in contravention 
of the Law on the Census applied to citizens belonging to 
national communities. 

</TEXT>

