<H3> <TI>   Two Finance Deputies Replaced </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Two Finance Deputies Replaced </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2706082294 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 0600 
GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2706082294 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] During the Warsaw Radio morning slot "Signals of 
the Day" today, Grzegorz Kolodko, deputy prime minister and 
finance minister, confirmed that there have been personnel 
changes in his ministry. Two deputy ministers--Wojciech Misiag 
and Henryk Chmielak--have been dismissed. 
  [Begin Kolodko recording] Today I am handing a thank you 
letter to Dr. Chmielak and Minister Misiag, who will now be 
working in a different capacity. This is in connection with 
certain changes arising from the implementation of the Strategy 
for Poland program, which is now official and has been adopted 
by the Sejm. They are leading experts and we do not have enough 
of them. They will be helping us out, using their experience, 
expertise, and qualifications in a different way. 
  At 0805, on behalf of Prime Minister Pawlak, I will be 
making 
appropriate nominations. Dr. Krzysztof Kalicki from the Main 
School of Commerce, a leading expert in monetary policy, will be 
appointed as first deputy finance minister and secretary of 
state. Professor Elzbieta Chojna-Duch, from the Law Department 
at Warsaw University, who was until now my adviser on budget 
policy, will be appointed under secretary of state, with 
responsibility for supervising the budget sector. 
  I would like to add that these are not the only changes. 
These are the changes that are being implemented today in this 
ministry. [end recording] [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

