<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Union of Labor To Join Opposition </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Union of Labor To Join Opposition </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2606163494 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1600 
GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2606163494 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The National Council of the Union of Labor [UP] has 
made a decision on joining the opposition to Prime Minister 
Waldemar Pawlak's government. UP has accused the government 
coalition of failing to implement the policies announced during 
the election campaign and of continuing the policies of the 
previous governments. UP has also criticized the government's 
Strategy for Poland program. According to UP, this document 
assumes a further exacerbation of the uneven distribution of the 
social costs of the transformation of the state. 
  The UP National Council has not yet decided whether Industry 
Minister Marek Pol, who represents UP in the government, should 
leave the Council of Ministers. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

