<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pawlak Signs Decree on Implementing `Strategy' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pawlak Signs Decree on Implementing `Strategy' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406202994 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1949 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2406202994 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 24 Jun--On 20 June, Prime Minister Waldemar 
Pawlak signed a decree on preparing the implementation of 
"Strategy for Poland," the government plan for socioeconomic 
policy for the years 1994-97, the Government Press Office 
reported this evening. 
  On the basis of the decree on the introduction and 
implementation of "Stretegy for Poland", ministers and heads of 
central administrative offices will, by 25 June, prepare lists 
of ministerial tasks ensuant upon "Strategy," the drafts of new 
legislative documents, and indispensible changes to legislation 
already in existence. Supervision over the preparatory work has 
been entrusted to the secretary of the Council of Minister's 
Economic Committee [KERM]. 
  The timetable of activities making possible the introduction 
and implementation of the government program, prepared on the 
basis of ministerial materials, will be presented to the Council 
of Ministers by the KERM secretary by 5 July of this year, reads 
the Government Press Office communique. 

</TEXT>

