<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sejm Passes Law on Currency Redenomination </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sejm Passes Law on Currency Redenomination </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2506143194 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1054 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2506143194 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Warsaw, 25 June--The Sejm passed a law on 
redenomination of the zloty today. With effect from 1 January 
1995, "old zlotys" will be gradually replaced by new notes and 
coins. The new zloty will be divided into 100 groszy, and its 
value will be the equivalent of the present 10,000 zlotys. The 
law was passed with 306 votes for, one against, and one 
abstention. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

