<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moravcik, Meciar View Political Scene </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moravcik, Meciar View Political Scene </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2606160294 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1500 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2606160294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1500 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Slovak coalition and opposition dealt with the 
first hundred days of the government's rule in today's "Kroky" 
[Steps] TV program. Prime Minister Jozef Moravcik pointed out 
that the functioning of a parliamentary democracy requires a 
stable structure of political parties, which is an important 
prerequisite for political stability. According to him, the 
coming elections can also play an important role from the point 
of view of sharpening the profile of the political scene. Jozef 
Moravcik stated that the Left is forming well and that the Right 
of the political spectrum is also clear. However, he said that 
the situation is difficult in the center, where a rather 
complicated development can yet be expected. 
  Vladimir Meciar, chairman of the Movement for a Democratic 
Slovakia, described the coalition government as a broad-based 
experiment that cannot be maintained over the longer term. He 
said of Jozef Moravcik's Cabinet that it is heading for economic 
ruin in going back to a given macroeconomic policy, that it is 
incompetent in the financial sphere, and that it is coping badly 
with privatization. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

