<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ganic Urges U.S. Senate To Lift Arms Embargo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ganic Urges U.S. Senate To Lift Arms Embargo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406213994 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 2000 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2406213994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Speaking in the U.S. Senate in connection with a 
debate on lifting the arms embargo in Bosnia-Herzegovina, Ejup 
Ganic, vice president of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Federation, said 
inter alia that the arms embargo against the legitimate and 
recognized Government of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Republic was the 
policy aimed at the therapy that the international community has 
been employing in Bosnia-Herzegovina in the past two years in 
response to the aggression. This therapy has led to a 
catastrophe in my country. The therapy failed simply because 
the patient is dying and it must be changed. 
  Repression and genocide against the non-Serb population are 
part of the program of creating a greater Serbia on the basis of 
the idea of ethnic cleansing. Unfortunately, 50 years later, 
Europe is again witnessing the expansion of fascism. We are 
asking you to lift the embargo so that we can exclusively defend 
ourselves and ensure a lasting peace. We have not lost the war. 
The Serbs have tried to destroy our country and us with all 
available means, but they have not yet succeeded in this. 
  Our people are capable and knowledgeable, and with their 
bare 
hands they are still resisting and keeping our main towns and 
vital industrial zones under their control. We are asking you 
to lift the embargo to create conditions for peace and for talks 
through balance in arms. We need arms in order to survive and 
not in order to win, because our losses and the genocide we 
suffered prevent us from speaking about victory. 
  For this reason we say it again and again: We are not asking 
your troops to fight for us on the ground, this is our task, but 
we are begging you not to use big words that translate into 
small actions. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

