<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gligorov Holds Talks With Owen, Stoltenberg </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2506121194 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1041 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2506121194 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Skopje, 25 Jun (TANJUG) -- Macedonian President Kiro 
Gligorov received Lord David Owen and Thorvald Stoltenberg, 
cochairmen of the Geneva conference on former Yugoslavia, at 
their request in Skopje this morning, an announcement from the 
president's office says. 
  The talks focused on several issues of relevance to the 
situation in the region of former Yugoslavia and the 
international mediators' mission. These issues were also 
discussed at the European Union summit in Corfu, from where Lord 
Owen and Stoltenberg have just arrived. 
  TANJUG has learned that Gligorov and the two cochairmen also 
discussed the dire economic situation in The Former Yugoslav 
Republic of Macedonia [FYROM] caused by the economic sanctions 
against the FRY [Federal Republic of Yugoslavia], Greece's trade 
embargo, and the situation in the border area between the FYROM 
and the FRY. 

</TEXT>

