<H3> <TI>   Owen Says FYROM Discussed at Corfu Summit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Owen Says FYROM Discussed at Corfu Summit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2506171794 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1556 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2506171794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Skopje, 25 June (TANJUG) -- "We mentioned the 
problem of Macedonia's [The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia -- FYROM] northern border with Serbia during the Corfu 
talks. We decided to discuss this issue in detail and, if 
possible, to resolve it appropriately," said Lord Owen, 
cochairman of the conference on former Yugoslavia, today during 
his brief meeting with the press in Skopje. 
  According to Owen, the European Union "is striving to 
prevent 
another war, in addition the Bosnian one, and that is the 
Serb-Croat war, which was one of the main items on the Corfu 
summit agenda, besides the situation in Ukraine." 
  Owen said that Macedonia was discussed at the summit in 
connection with the cochairmen's and international envoys' 
efforts to organize direct negotiations with Greece and that 
Macedonia needs aid, economic aid in particular. "All of us 
involved in the negotiating process will support this," Lord 
Owen said. 

</TEXT>

