<H3> <TI>   State Assets Agency Chairman Resigns </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    State Assets Agency Chairman Resigns </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2806073694 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
0700 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2806073694 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tibor Pongracz, chairman of the board of directors 
of the State Assets Agency [AVU], has resigned. The state 
secretary for privatization is the fourth member of the board of 
directors to step down from his position. The 11-member body 
has thereby decreased in size to seven. 
  Tibor Pongracz told NEPSZABADSAG that the prime minister 
accepted his resignation with effect from 1 July. The AVU's 
board of directors is still capable of making decisions because 
six members are sufficient for decisionmaking. 

</TEXT>

