<F P=100> SLOVENIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Drnovsek Accepts Justice Minister's Resignation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Drnovsek Accepts Justice Minister's Resignation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2706144794 Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network in Slovene 
1330 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2706144794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Slovene </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] We have just learned that Prime Minister Janez 
Drnovsek has accepted the resignation of Justice Minister Miha 
Kozinc. In the coming days, the prime minister will inform the 
State Chamber about this and propose a new candidate for justice 
minister. The prime minister has asked the relevant government 
expert services to prepare a statement for the next government 
session and an assessment of the work of the Housing Commission, 
as well as to prepare guidelines for forming and adopting all 
necessary documents regarding the problem. This was said in the 
public announcement the prime minister's Cabinet has just issued. 

</TEXT>

