<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   NDP Calls For `Federalization' of FYROM </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NDP Calls For `Federalization' of FYROM </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2706161094 Skopje MIC in English 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2706161094 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MIC </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "NDP Proposing Federalization of </F>
Macedonia"] 
  [Text] The annual conference of the National Democratic 
Party [NDP] (ethnic Albanians) held in Tetovo last Saturday [25 
June] finished with an adoption of a 9-point memorandum. NDP is 
not satisfied with the democratic processes going on in 
Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM], 
particularly since the disintegration of Yugoslavia. This party 
is emphasizing that the Albanian people have been deprived of 
the right for self- orientation, although they are the third 
largest nation in the former Yugoslavia. 
  The memorandum condemns the manipulations by the government 
in relation to the census of the population. The NDP concludes 
that these manipulations are aimed at discrediting the Albanian 
political factor before the international institutions, as well 
as its further splitting apart. 
  The NDP underlined the government's responsibility for the 
further building up and functioning of the state and community 
institutions on a one-national basis. This, the NDP believes, 
legalizes the political discrediting and tolerance of the 
advents of neofascism. Otherwise, the NDP is pushing for a 
federalization of Macedonia and the formation of an autonomous 
region Ilirida in Macedonia. 
  Guests from the PDP fraction were also present at the 
conference, as well as representatives from the Demo-Christian 
Party of Kosovo and the Democratic Party and Social Democratic 
Party from Albania. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

