<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Work by Albanian Census Takers Delayed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Work by Albanian Census Takers Delayed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2706161294 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2706161294 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Census 1994"] </F>
  [Text] Even five days after the census began, the situation 
has not essentially changed, especially in regions inhabited 
mostly by Albanians (Tetovo, Gostivar). Communal census 
instructors and clerks are still awaiting their political 
leaders' views before they go out and do their job. Local 
census committees insist on having only Albanian census clerks 
in "pure ethnic regions." Due to the delay, they also request 
postponement of the operation for as many days as it has thus 
far been put off. 
  The census is carried out normally in all remaining cities. 
As the Macedonian television reports, the State Statistics 
Institute informs that 338,599 citizens, 98,593 households, 
104,155 apartments and 39,430 farms have been registered up to 
June 29, inclusive. Parallel with the census in Macedonia [The 
Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] is the census of 
Macedonians throughout the world who have valid documents, 
regardless of the date of issuance. This operation is carried 
out in 10 foreign countries in which Macedonia has diplomatic 
offices, in three countries in which it has only representative 
offices, and all countries whose authorities gave permission for 
the census to be realized. Reports from these countries 
indicate a need of prolonging the deadline. Some sources inform 
Macedonian citizens of Albanian origin in Switzerland and 
Germany have announced their intention to boycott the census. 
No census of Macedonians was allowed in Federal Yugoslavia by 
the authorities there. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

