<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Transportation Agreement Signed With Albania </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Transportation Agreement Signed With Albania </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2706164894 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2706164894 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Changes in Road Traffic With Albania"] </F>
  [Text] Starting 1 July, the traffic between Albania and 
Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] 
will be facilitated -- drivers will only be required transport 
licenses. This was agreed on in Ohrid, during the recent 
meeting between road traffic experts of the Albanian Ministry 
for Transport and Communication and the Macedonian Ministry of 
City Planning, Construction, Traffic, and Ecology. All 
Macedonian transporting firms will be exempted from paying road 
taxes and tolls. The first contingent of 5,000 transportation 
licenses, bilateral and transit, as well as 100 licenses for 
transportation to and from third countries, is already being 
distributed. 
  At the Ohrid meeting, the two sides also signed a draft 
agreement on international transport of passengers and goods 
through both countries. The agreement was signed in Albanian, 
Macedonian, and English. The Albanian side, however, had 
remarks on the name of Republic of Macedonia being used in the 
text, so they introduced a special clause on the agreement 
coming into effect after the additional consultations on the 
problem. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

