<H3> <TI>   Silajdzic Meets With Italian Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Silajdzic Meets With Italian Foreign Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2706122794 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1200 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2706122794 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Italian Foreign Minister Antonio Martino has held 
talks in Sarajevo with Bosnia-Herzegovina Prime Minister Haris 
Silajdzic. After the talks Prime Minister Silajdzic said that 
the external borders of Bosnia-Herzegovina cannot be haggled 
over and cannot be the subject of any political negotiations. 
According to him, this message was clearly conveyed to the 
Italian foreign minister. It was stressed that only an internal 
transformation of Bosnia-Herzegovina can be discussed. 
  The Italian minister said that he has come to Sarajevo to 
conduct preparations for the September meeting of G-7 and Russia 
[in Naples]. He did not comment on the current proposals on the 
resolution of the crisis in Bosnia-Herzegovina, but said that 
the situation will be discussed in detail at the Naples meeting. 

</TEXT>

