<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Abdic Pledges To Set Up Resistance Front </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Abdic Pledges To Set Up Resistance Front </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2706145294 Pale Srpski Radio-Televizija Studio Sarajevo 
Radio in Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2706145294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pale Srpski Radio-Televizija Studio Sarajevo 
Radio </F>

<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Fikret Abdic, the president of the autonomous 
province of western Bosnia [APWB], told Velkaton Radio in Velika 
Kladusa this morning that the army of the autonomous province of 
western Bosnia is objectively not able to prove to the world the 
justness of its struggle against the brutal aggression of the 
rebel army loyal to Izetbegovic's authorities. Slavisa Sabljic 
has a report. 
  [Sabljic] Abdic said that the idea of autonomy was supported 
by Muslims in the diaspora, but not by the diplomatic 
authorities in Sarajevo which, via their primitive sympathizers, 
have opted for the war and the bloody quenching of our army's 
struggle for its own province and autonomy. The ignominious 
action and the rebels' offensive that began on 10 June had been 
prepared for months, Abdic went on to say and stressed that the 
offensive's final aim was to strangulate the province and 
liquidate the province's leaders. However, Abdic said, it is 
impossible to strangulate the province, there can only arise an 
all-people's resistance front, which we will organize. 
  Stressing the fabrications, media madness, and the lies that 
certain media spread to the international public, Abdic said at 
the end of his interview on Velkaton Radio that the REUTER 
agency blazed the trail in spreading lies about Muslim conflicts 
in the province. A REUTER team of journalists will soon arrive 
in Kladusa in order to, as Abdic put it, deny their own reports. 

</TEXT>

