<H3> <TI>   HZDS Sets Out Possible Coalition Partners </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    HZDS Sets Out Possible Coalition Partners </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2506213094 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1630 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2506213094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1630 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Republican Council of the Movement for a 
Democratic Slovakia [HZDS] held a session at Stara Lesna in the 
High Tatras today. It discussed the current political 
situation, preparation for the parliamentary elections, and 
coalition cooperation. Our correspondent Pavol Sveton is on the 
line to report from there: 
  [Sveton] [passage omitted] HZDS Deputy Chairman Sergej 
Kozlik 
said that the HZDS was at present stronger than in 1992. 
Following an agreement with the Farmers Party of Slovakia 
[Rolnicka Strana Slovenska--RSS] on election coalition 
cooperation, the HZDS also counts on cooperation with the Slovak 
National Party [SNS], provided it passes the election threshold, 
as well as with the KDH [Christian Democratic Movement] and the 
Party of the Democratic Left [SDL]. The HZDS is open to the 
option of cooperating with the Association of the Workers of 
Slovakia [Zdruzenie Robotnikov Slovenska], the Forum of Workers 
[Forum Robotnikov], the Christian Social Union [KSU], and with 
civic associations and interest groups in districts--such as the 
Union of Antifascist Fighters. The HZDS also considers possible 
cooperation with the New Slovakia movement. 
  At a news conference today, it was said that an election 
program was currently being drafted. It should be ready in 
three weeks' time and be capable of addressing every single 
citizen and individual region of Slovakia. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

