<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Agreements Signed With Albanian Prime Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Agreements Signed With Albanian Prime Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2706124794 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1200 
GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2706124794 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Czech </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ivana Anyzova reports on today's talks between Czech 
Prime Minister Vaclav Klaus and Albanian Prime Minister 
Aleksander Meksi. 
  [Anyzova] The two prime ministers signed an agreement on 
trade and technical relations and one on the support and mutual 
protection of investments. They exchanged information about the 
situation in their countries, foreign policy initiatives, and 
bilateral relations. They expressed a wish to develop mutual 
contacts in science, culture, and tourism. They also agreed 
that the Czech side will grant Albania a long-term loan to 
purchase farming and food-processing equipment. 
  Although economic cooperation has receded over recent years, 
our side regards as advantageous the fact that Czech goods have 
been offered to Albanian agriculture and the food-processing 
industry. 
  Vaclav Klaus emphasized that such cooperation is a useful 
form of policy aimed at boosting exports. 

</TEXT>

