<H3> <TI>   Arrival of Turkish Troops Postponed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arrival of Turkish Troops Postponed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2806113194 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1000 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2806113194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Split, Croatia June 28 (A.A.) -- The transfer of 
Turkish troops to Zenica, Bosnia-Herzegovina, was postponed 
today because of problems concerning the renting of living 
quarters for the troops. All preparations for the transfer have 
been concluded. 
  The first group of Turkish forces which will join the UN 
peacekeeping forces arrived in Split June 22. The second 
contingent left for Split, on June 24. 
  The first contingent brought with it 260 tons of weapons and 
equipment, 50 small vehicles, 139 large vehicles, armored 
personnel carriers, and 19 trailers. 

</TEXT>

