<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry Officials Relieved of Posts </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Ministry Officials Relieved of Posts </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2906043694 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
2000 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2906043694 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Minister of Defense Lajos Fur and Laszlo Szendrei, 
political state secretary at the Ministry of Defense, have said 
farewell to leaders of the Ministry of Defense and the Hungarian 
Army at a staff meeting. 
  At the meeting Army Commander Janos Deak, speaking about the 
new leadership, expounded the view that all arrivals who take up 
the cause of defense would be accepted at the ministry. It was 
also announced that Zoltan Pecze, deputy state secretary at the 
Ministry of Defense, would be relieved from his post, effective 
the middle of July. 
  Csaba Hende, state secretary at Prime Minister's Office, and 
Laszlo Szoeke, head of the Rehabilitation Office, have also been 
relieved from their posts, effective mid-July. They have all 
waived their claim to the lump sum payment to which they are 
eligible in accordance with the law on civil servants. 

