<F P=106> [Report by Antoaneta Puncheva] </F>
  [Text] The National Coordinating Council of the SDS [Union 
of Democratic Forces] today discussed the resolution of the SDS 
parliamentary group analyzing the boycott of parliament and the 
negative assessment of a large number of SDS deputies on taking 
part in full parliamentary sessions on a selective basis. In 
the view of the National Coordinating Council, in the future 
authorized members of the SDS parliamentary group should enter 
the plenary hall of parliament to represent SDS interests. 
Today the SDS deputies hotly debated their strategy for three 
hours, but failed to reach any decision. 
  The Ecoglasnost National Movement has disseminated an 
address 
in which it declares that it supports the decision adopted by 
the Sixth SDS National Conference to boycott parliament and 
conduct extraparliamentary actions. 

