<F P=103> AU2806181794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Bulgarian Socialist Party [BSP] Press Center 
has reported that President Zhelyu Zhelev today met with a group 
of National Assembly deputies of the BSP, who handed him a 
petition with the signatures of 122 deputies from all the 
political parties represented in parliament requesting him to 
pardon Georgi Atanasov and Stoyan Ovcharov [prime minister and 
minister of economics and planning in final years of Zhivkov 
regime], who are now serving prison sentences. According to the 
BSP deputies, when President Zhelev has discussed the material 
evidence submitted on the state of health of the two prisoners 
and considered the signatories to the petition, he should decide 
to sign a decree pardoning the two former state officials. The 
group of deputies found that the president showed understanding 
for their request and expect a favorable result to the petition 
in the very near future. 
  According to a second fax we received from the Presidency, 
the Press Center of the Presidency makes the following 
announcement in connection with the announcement by the BSP 
Press Center on the meeting between President Zhelyu Zhelev and 
a group of BSP deputies: Bulgarian President has received a 
petition handed to him requesting pardons for Georgi Atanasov 
and Stoyan Ovcharov. 

