<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry Receives Turkish Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Ministry Receives Turkish Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2706164194 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1500 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2706164194 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Delegations from the Croatian and Turkish Defense 
Ministries have held talks in Zagreb on promoting bilateral 
cooperation. Croatian Deputy Defense Minister Josip Juras 
received the Turkish Defense Ministry delegation. 
  The Turkish delegation, led by Colonel General Teoman Ekran, 
held talks with Brigadier General Janko Bobetko, the chief of 
the General Staff of the Croatian Army; and Brig. Gen. Antun 
Tus, the main military adviser to the Croatian president. 
  After the talks Josip Juras said that the two delegations 
had 
discussed military and technical cooperation and aid, as well as 
cooperation at experts' level. He added that some very concrete 
agreements had been reached, and he believed they would 
materialize in the near future, in the interest of both 
countries. 
  The aim of our visit is to strengthen relations between 
Croatia and Turkey and discuss possibilities for cooperation 
between the two ministries, Ekran said. 

</TEXT>

