<H3> <TI>   Milosevic Praises Party for Joining Government </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Milosevic Praises Party for Joining Government </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2906030494 Belgrade TANJUG in English 2140 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2906030494 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, June 28 (TANJUG) -- Serbian President 
Slobodan Milosevic on Tuesday praised the opposition New 
Democracy Party for supporting the idea of a national unity 
government by joining the cabinet of Premier Mirko Marjanovic. 
  Milosevic said that the party had acted from patriotic 
motives, rising above petty party interests. Milosevic was 
speaking with the party's representatives whom he received on 
the occasion of 100 days in office of the Serbian government. He 
had first received Prime Minister Marjanovic and his cabinet. 
  After the meeting, New Democracy president Dusan Mihajlovic 
told reporters the party had no reason to be dissatisfied with 
the decision to join the cabinet. Mihajlovic said the party had 
accepted the offer to join the Marjanovic cabinet because of the 
latter's promise to work actively for peace, the lifting of 
international sanctions against Yugoslavia (Serbia/Montenegro), 
its reintegration in the international economic and political 
community and the implementation of the country's economic 
recovery programme. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

