<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moravcik Answers Meciar's Criticism of Trips </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moravcik Answers Meciar's Criticism of Trips </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2806161394 Bratislava PRAVDA in Slovak 21 Jun 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU2806161394 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava PRAVDA </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "Jozef Moravcik Versus Vladimir Meciar"] </F>
  [Text] Bratislava--In an interview for the TA SR, Prime 
Minister Jozef Moravcik yesterday described as very incompetent 
former Prime Minister Vladimir Meciar's allegations, made in an 
interview for SMENA NA NEDELU, that the official tours of duty 
of current government officials were "tourism for taxpayers' 
money." Moravcik stated that, if he were to compare official 
trips before [under Meciar's government, when he was foreign 
minister] and now, the present ones are far more concentrated 
and businesslike. He specified that one of the serious 
shortcomings under Vladimir Meciar's government was that, from 
the viewpoint of diplomatic practice, official trips were not of 
the required standard. Moravcik stated that, throughout his term 
as prime minister, Meciar did not pay a single official visit to 
any country of the European Union [EU] because of the lack of an 
official invitation. In that sense, Moravcik's visit to France 
was the first official trip made by a Slovak prime minister to 
an EU country since the founding of the independent Slovak 
Republic. 
  According to Moravcik, the trips of the other Cabinet 
ministers can be positively evaluated as well. The level at 
which they are being received is higher than was the case of 
representatives of the previous cabinet. 

</TEXT>

