<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Baudys Says Planned Defense Cuts on Target </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Baudys Says Planned Defense Cuts on Target </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2806160794 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1100 
GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2806160794 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Czech </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At the present time, all of the prerequisites exist 
in the Czech Army for the reduction of the Armed Forces to the 
planned 65,000 in 1995, Defense Minister Antonin Baudys said 
today. He said that, over the past 18 months, the number of 
troops was reduced from just below 106,000 to 88,000 men under 
arms. Key posts on strategic and operational levels were filled 
with uncompromised and professionally trained generals and 
officers, Baudys said. 

</TEXT>

