<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Debt Agreement Signed With London Club </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Debt Agreement Signed With London Club </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2906094594 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 0800 
GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2906094594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At an official ceremony at the Boyana residence on 
29 June, Finance Minister Stoyan Aleksandrov signed the 
documents on settling the country's foreign debt to the London 
Club creditors. Peter Tils, Deutsche Bank executive director, 
and Dr. Hans-Dirk Kleckerer of the Deutsche Bank signed the 
basic agreements that regulate the replacement of our present 
debts to the banks by state securities, or reduced payments. 
  Lee Warner, director of settlements for Citibank in New 
York, 
signed an agreement on the fiscal aspects of the settlement, the 
reduced initial interest payments, and the postponed interest 
payments. 
  Representatives of 12 banks, which are our basic creditors 
from the London Club, signed an annex to the agreement that 
settles our direct debts to them. The ceremony was attended by 
Prime Minister Lyuben Berov. 

</TEXT>

