<H3> <TI>   KDNP Elects Interim Presidium; Surjan Chairman </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    KDNP Elects Interim Presidium; Surjan Chairman </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2606185894 Budapest MTI in English 1737 GMT 25 Jun 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2606185894 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, June 25 (MTI) -- The presidium of the 
Christian Democratic People's Party (KDNP) has tendered its 
resignation. 
  In its place, the KDNP National Board elected a smaller 
interim presidium with a six-month mandate in Budapest today. 
  The National Board re-elected Laszlo Surjan as party 
chairman. 
  In the May elections, the Christian Democrats won 22 seats 
in 
Hungary's 386-member parliament, corresponding to 5.7 per cent 
of the mandates. Both the party leadership and the members were 
dissatisfied with the result. 
  The mandate of the interim presidium will expire within 60 
days after the municipal elections this autumn but not later 
than on December 15. 
  Surjan told the press that the KDNP would hold a national 
meeting in autumn to discuss the party's political renewal, 
decide on structural changes, and revise the party rules. 

</TEXT>

