  [Text] Prishtina, June 27 (ATA) -- The interrogation of 14 
Albanians accused of allegedly forming the Ministry of Defence 
of the Republic of Kosova ended after eight sittings in the 
Prishtina Court. In the last sittings, all the accused rejected 
as a whole the indictment brought against them. They explained 
in detail that they were severely treated by the State Security, 
saying that the accusation was based on slanders and statements 
made in the Investigation Office under pressure. 
  The other sitting of this framed trial will be held on June 
27 with the interrogation of the witnesses. 

