<H3> <TI>   Berisha Comments on `Great' Economic Growth </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Berisha Comments on `Great' Economic Growth </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2806110394 Tirana ATA in English 1020 GMT 28 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2806110394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, June 28 (ATA) -- The achievement of a rapid 
economic growth constitutes our greatest trial, it is a historic 
challenge that we must win, President Berisha said yesterday at 
the National Council of the Democratic Party in Tirana. Mr. 
Berisha said that the achievement of a rapid economic growth 
will also assure to make up for the lost valuable time. 
  Referring to an IMF information last February which ranked 
Albania the first in Europe for the rapid economic growth of 
about 10 percent, Mr. Berisha said that realization of these 
short term rapid rates marks a great achievement for Albania and 
that a long term, not short term, guarantee of these high norms 
and rates will be Archimedean Screw for its integration into the 
bosom of the developed countries of Europe. 
  Although the Albanian economy will continue for many years 
to 
have a real income and consumption per capita among the lowest 
one in Europe, an open economic policy based on freedom would 
help maintain an economic growth of 8-10 percent per annum and 
for a long -term period, President Berisha said, basing the 
rapid economic growth on the intellectual potential, 
geographical position, natural resources and a favourable market 
of labour power at home. 

</TEXT>

