<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Hungary </F>
<H3> <TI>   Horn Tasked To Form Government </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Horn Tasked To Form Government </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2806150494 Budapest MTI in English 1406 GMT 28 Jun 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2806150494 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 28 June (MTI) -- At the founding session 
of Parliament this afternoon, Prime Minister Peter Boross 
formally announced the expiration of his cabinet's mandate. The 
erstwhile cabinet will continue on for a short time as a 
caretaker government with limited powers. 
  After this procedure, President Arpad Goncz commissioned 
Hungarian Socialist Party Chairman Gyula Horn to form a new 
government. 
  Horn formally accepted the commission, and announced that he 
would present the program of the new government to Parliament 
within a short time. 

</TEXT>

