<H3> <TI>   MSZP, SZDSZ Publish Cabinet List </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MSZP, SZDSZ Publish Cabinet List </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2406160094 Budapest MTI in English 1522 GMT 24 Jun 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2406160094 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 24 June (MTI) -- The Hungarian Socialist 
Party and the Alliance of Free Democrats signed the two-party 
coalition agreement a little before 4.30 P.M. local time on 
Friday [24 June]. 
  The document was signed by chairmen Gyula Horn and Ivan 
Peto. 
  The parties agreed on the line-up of the new government. 
  The cabinet list is as follows: 


Cabinet List 

Prime Minister                               Gyula Horn 

Minister of the Interior                     Gabor Kuncze (also coalition 
                                             deputy prime minister) 

Minister of Finance                          Laszlo Bekesi 

Minister of Industry and Trade               Laszlo Pal 

Minister of Transport, Telecommunications,   Karoly Lotz 
and Water Management 

Minister of Agriculture                      Laszlo Lakos 

Minister of Labor                            Mrs. Magda Kosa 

Minister of Environment and Regional         Ferenc Baja 
Policy 

Minister of Defence                          Gyorgy Keleti 

Minister of Foreign Affairs                  Laszlo Kovacs 

Minister of Justice                          Pal Vastagh 

Minister of Culture and Education            Gabor Fodor 

Minister of Welfare                          Pal Kovacs 

Minister without portfolio in charge of      Bela Katona 
National Security Office 



</TEXT>

